HEADWORD: Circumincession
<hw>Cir`cum*in*ces"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>circum-</ets> + L. <ets>incedere</ets>, <ets>incessum</ets>, to
walk.]</ety> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>The reciprocal existence in each
other of the three persons of the Trinity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumjacence</ent>⟦br⟧
